and","Seckington, Warwickshire, England":"Seckington, Warwickshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Burdett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Midlands, of Norman origin): perhaps from an Old French personal name <i>Burdet</i>, a pet form of an unrecorded ancient Germanic name, <i>Burdo</i>, or from Gaulish <i>burdo</i> ‘mule’.","Altered form of French <b>Burdet</b> (see   Burdette  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Burditt","meanings":["English (Northamptonshire and Leicestershire, of Norman origin): variant of   Burdett  ."]},{"name":"Burdette","meanings":["English: altered form of   Burdett  .","Altered form of French <b>Burdet</b>, a cognate of   Burdin  . Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"Burden","meanings":["English:","(southern England, of Norman origin): from a diminutive of the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Burdo</i>, for which compare   Burdett  . <i>Burdonus</i> and other derivatives of the Gaulish personal name <i>Burdo</i> (‘mule’) are found in France, where it is rare and the similar French surname may derive instead from Old French <i>bourdon</i> in the sense ‘pilgrim's staff’ (compare   Bourdon   1). The personal name, whether of ancient Germanic or Gaulish origin, does occur in medieval England, but rarely.","habitational name from any of various places called Burdon or Burden. Burden in Yorkshire and Great Burdon in County Durham are named with Old English <i>burh</i> ‘stronghold, fortified place’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’; Burdon in Tyne and Wear is named with Old English <i>b̄re</i> ‘byre’ + <i>denu</i> ‘valley’."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":35,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Burdett Sir was born in 1347, in Seckington, Warwickshire, England, his father, Robert Burdett, was 22 and his mother, Elizabeth Garshill, was 21. He married Katherine Arderne in 1365, in Alvanley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in April 1403, in his hometown, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1347–April 1403":"1347–aprill 1403","1347–1403":"1347–1403","1322–1385":"1322–1385","1384–1419":"1384–1419","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1403":"1403","1347":"1347","1325":"1325","1322":"1322","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","after 1385":"pärast 1385","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","April 1403":"aprill 1403","Delves, Staffordshire, England":"Delves, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alvanley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Alvanley, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gorworth, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Seckington, Warwickshire, England":"Seckington, Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"1347–April 1403":"1347–huhtikuu 1403","1347–1403":"1347–1403","1322–1385":"1322–1385","1384–1419":"1384–1419","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1403":"1403","1347":"1347","1325":"1325","1322":"1322","1365":"1365","1385":"1385","1384":"1384","after 1385":"1385 jälkeen","1382":"1382","1419":"1419","April 1403":"huhtikuu 1403","Delves, Staffordshire, England":"Delves, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Alvanley, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Alvanley, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Gorworth, Cheshire, England":"Che